## Permitted Purpose

A "Permitted Purpose" is any purpose other than a Competing Use. A
"Competing Use" is making the Software available to third parties as a
hosted or embedded service that competes with the Licensor's paid
version(s) of the Software. For the avoidance of doubt, Competing Use
does NOT include:

  1. Use for internal purposes by employees and contractors of your business.
  2. Use by customers of your business for their own internal purposes.
  3. Use to develop software that is not made available to third parties.
  4. Personal use, including for research or experimentation.
  5. Security review, auditing, vulnerability disclosure, or academic study.

